you your whole life,

24:57.400 --> 24:58.925
they're breathing,

24:59.760 --> 25:01.922
present, and then
they're just gone.

25:02.880 --> 25:04.848
Totally gone.
Vanished.

25:04.920 --> 25:06.809
Never even get to
see 'em again.

25:06.880 --> 25:08.882
Ever. That sucks.

25:09.560 --> 25:11.961
It's a really bad plan,
whoever came up with it.

25:18.600 --> 25:21.171
I think grief is just the
period of time it takes

25:21.240 --> 25:22.924
for your brain to accept
that someone's gone.

25:24.560 --> 25:26.847
'Cause everything in
your body, your mind,

25:26.960 --> 25:28.610
your entire being, just
keeps bringing you back

25:28.680 --> 25:31.001
to the moment that
they're still alive.

25:31.360 --> 25:33.647
Takes a long time for your
body to let go of that.

25:34.520 --> 25:36.170
That's exactly
what it is.

25:36.840 --> 25:38.285
It's the hardest
thing of all,

25:39.320 --> 25:41.209
to let go of
someone you love.

25:43.440 --> 25:45.408
I like being
with you, Norman.

25:57.440 --> 25:59.169
Hey, I wonder whose
hand they found.

25:59.560 --> 26:00.641
What hand?

26:01.320 --> 26:06.008
Um, they found a decomposing
hand in a fisherman's net.

26:07.840 --> 26:10.002
(STAMMERING) Do they
know whose hand it was?

26:10.280 --> 26:11.486
No, just...

26:12.480 --> 26:14.323
...some man's hand.

26:23.920 --> 26:25.843
Mother! Mother!
(GASPING)

26:28.000 --> 26:29.081
What?

26:29.160 --> 26:31.242
Mother, they found a hand
in a fisherman's net!

26:31.360 --> 26:32.521
A man's hand.

26:35.000 --> 26:37.162
Don't go there.
You're panicking.

26:37.280 --> 26:39.567
It's just a hand. It could be
a million different hands.

26:41.800 --> 26:43.245
(DOORBELL RINGS)

26:55.320 --> 26:57.721
Mrs. Bates, we need you to come
with us down to the station.

26:59.160 --> 27:00.207
Why?

27:02.840 --> 27:05.320
Sheriff Romero would like
to ask you a few questions.

27:20.120 --> 27:21.724
(KEYS JANGLING)

27:22.600 --> 27:23.647
(DOOR OPENS)

27:31.360 --> 27:32.566
(SIGHS)

27:35.160 --> 27:36.810
I need you to tell
me what happened.

27:38.240 --> 27:39.366
Well, uh...

27:42.320 --> 27:44.322
I was just at home.

27:45.520 --> 27:46.885
Uh...

27:46.960 --> 27:50.328
The police came and told me
that you wanted to talk to me.

27:50.400 --> 27:52.209
I don't mean what
happened just now.

27:52.280 --> 27:54.248
I mean, what happened
the night that...

27:54.360 --> 27:55.646
That Keith Summers
went missing.

27:56.000 --> 27:57.729
But I told you
everything I know.

27:59.400 --> 28:00.447
Okay-

28:01.480 --> 28:03.244
We found
carpet fibers

28:03.320 --> 28:05.368
under the watch of
the recovered hand.

28:05.680 --> 28:07.170
We're gonna match 'em
to the carpeting

28:07.240 --> 28:09.242
that you were pulling
up out of your motel

28:09.320 --> 28:10.765
the night that
Keith disappeared.

28:12.280 --> 28:15.887
(SIGHS SLOWLY)

28:16.480 --> 28:18.005
Well, have fun
doing that.

28:22.240 --> 28:23.526
I'm... I'm trying
to help you here.

28:23.600 --> 28:24.726
Okay, I know
you did it.

28:24.800 --> 28:26.848
How could you
possibly know that,

28:26.920 --> 28:28.445
especially since I
didn't do it?

28:28.560 --> 28:30.722
I know it because I've been
doing this for 20 years,

28:30.800 --> 28:33.485
and I know people. I get
them on the inside.

28:33.560 --> 28:35.801
It's like a gift. And
I know you did it.

28:36.960 --> 28:38.928
Now, Keith wasn't
always a nice guy.

28:39.000 --> 28:41.321
I know that about him.
I know he was...

28:41.720 --> 28:43.961
He was involved in
a lot of things that...

28:44.280 --> 28:46.044
Any number of which could
have gotten him killed.

28:47.160 --> 28:48.366
But I also know
he wasn't happy

28:48.440 --> 28:50.727
about losing his home
and about you buying it.

28:51.680 --> 28:54.251
And he's the kind of guy
that might have tried to

28:54.320 --> 28:58.450
retaliate somehow, maybe
threaten you, scare you.

28:58.520 --> 29:00.568
I'm not scared.
Nobody scared me.

29:00.640 --> 29:02.244
He doesn't scare me,
and you don't scare me.

29:02.320 --> 29:04.084
I told you all that I know.
I told you I have

29:04.160 --> 29:05.844
nothing to do with this. Now,
can we be done with this now?

29:05.920 --> 29:08.321
Where'd you dump the carpeting
that you pulled up that night?

29:10.160 --> 29:11.241
I thought you said
you had it.

29:11.320 --> 29:12.845
No, I said
we're gonna test it.

29:16.080 --> 29:17.161
Well,

29:17.400 --> 29:20.927
how can you test it
if you don't have it?

29:21.000 --> 29:24.004
There's only three dumps it could
have wound up in. I'm gonna find it.

29:24.520 --> 29:26.921
But it'd be helpful to us,
and ultimately to you,

29:27.000 --> 29:28.729
if you were to
tell me where it is.

29:31.720 --> 29:33.563
I don't remember.
You don't remember?

29:33.640 --> 29:34.766
No, I don't.
You don't remember

29:34.840 --> 29:37.002
where you physically dumped
carloads full of carpeting?

29:37.080 --> 29:38.366
No, I don't.

29:45.000 --> 29:46.331
Okay, we're done now.

29:57.800 --> 30:00.121
NORMAN: The carpeting isn't still
gonna be in that dumpster.

30:00.200 --> 30:01.201
It might be.

30:01.320 --> 30:03.641
That was the first night we moved here.
It's not gonna be there.

30:03.720 --> 30:05.051
Fine, then it won't be.

30:06.400 --> 30:07.561
Whatever.

30:09.880 --> 30:11.120
Did you just
"whatever" me?

30:13.040 --> 30:14.530
What has gotten
into you?

30:14.600 --> 30:16.011
What, is it Dylan's doing?

30:16.080 --> 30:18.242
Is he... Has he
gotten to you?

30:22.720 --> 30:23.721
Look, we're here.

30:59.120 --> 31:01.168
Hi. I have a problem.

31:02.240 --> 31:05.449
I accidentally threw out my
wedding ring with the trash,

31:06.040 --> 31:07.883
and I put it on
the corner of

31:07.960 --> 31:10.531
Main and Hillcrest
in the dumpster.

31:10.600 --> 31:12.682
Can you tell me where
that trash is taken?

31:20.120 --> 31:23.647
(GASPING)
Oh, no.

31:26.640 --> 31:28.130
Oh, no.

31:28.800 --> 31:29.801
Mom, stop it!

31:31.760 --> 31:33.000
What am I supposed
to do, Norman?

31:33.120 --> 31:34.724
It's in there, and I can't get it!
Mom!

31:34.800 --> 31:35.926
Mom!

31:36.240 --> 31:38.811
(SCREAMING) I can't get it!
Mom! Mom!

31:39.680 --> 31:41.045
Shut up, Mom!

31:41.320 --> 31:42.321
This is your
own fault!

31:42.400 --> 31:44.004
I told you to call the police
the night it happened.

31:44.080 --> 31:45.844
I told you this is
a bad idea!

31:46.440 --> 31:47.965
You had every right
to defend yourself.

31:48.040 --> 31:49.246
But I didn't
defend myself.

31:49.320 --> 31:50.970
I killed the crap
out of him!

31:51.520 --> 31:54.091
I don't know why I did.
I was just so angry,

31:54.160 --> 31:55.924
angry that he would
come into my home,

31:56.000 --> 31:58.082
and then he would
do that to me!

31:58.160 --> 32:00.606
(GASPING AND CRYING)

32:05.640 --> 32:07.768
You don't
understand, Norman.

32:08.840 --> 32:10.888
My whole life...

32:10.960 --> 32:13.645
My whole life I've had
to put up with things.

32:15.480 --> 32:18.723
(GASPING AND CRYING)

32:21.040 --> 32:22.804
(SOBBING)

32:44.200 --> 32:45.964
(NORMA CONTINUES SOBBING)

33:07.240 --> 33:08.287
Hey-

33:09.560 --> 33:10.721
Hey-

33:14.720 --> 33:16.404
Why do you always
run away from me?

33:21.600 --> 33:22.681
I don't.

33:42.880 --> 33:45.121
(GAGS AND COUGHS)

33:45.440 --> 33:46.441
(LAUGHS)

33:48.760 --> 33:50.000
Don't laugh at me.

33:53.200 --> 33:54.725
I'm not. It's just...

33:56.720 --> 33:58.768
I'm sorry you had to
deal with her all alone.

34:00.160 --> 34:01.241
She's crazy.

34:01.600 --> 34:03.011
You have no idea, Dylan.

34:04.600 --> 34:05.647
What?

34:13.120 --> 34:14.724
That guy, Keith
Summers, the one...

34:14.800 --> 34:17.007
The one missing right
after we moved in.

34:17.520 --> 34:18.601
Yeah?

34:19.960 --> 34:22.246
He broke into the house
and attacked Mom.

34:22.960 --> 34:24.085
Raped her.

34:25.239 --> 34:26.241
What?

34:28.520 --> 34:30.123
I was out.

34:30.360 --> 34:31.929
I came home and found
her in the kitchen,

34:32.000 --> 34:33.161
her clothes torn off,

34:33.440 --> 34:35.090
her head
pushed into the table.

34:37.360 --> 34:41.284
I picked up this doorstop and hit
him on the head, and he passed out.

34:41.760 --> 34:44.366
She... She was
bleeding real bad.

34:44.440 --> 34:47.364
She cut her arm, I guess, so I
ran to get the first-aid kit.

34:48.840 --> 34:51.844
When I came back in the
room, she was stabbing him.

34:52.760 --> 34:55.525
Not once, like 30 times.
She totally lost it.

34:56.679 --> 35:00.082
She didn't want to call the cops, even
though I told her that we should.

35:01.200 --> 35:02.531
I'm so scared, Dylan.

35:04.480 --> 35:07.404
Every minute I've lived here,
every second, just total fear.

35:09.160 --> 35:11.891
And that Sheriff's totally
suspicious of her, and...

35:12.120 --> 35:14.043
And it's my fault.

35:15.520 --> 35:18.285
I... I did this
really stupid thing.

35:18.640 --> 35:20.130
Keith Summers,
he was, uh...

35:20.200 --> 35:23.283
He was wearing this, like, police
belt when he attacked Mom,

35:23.360 --> 35:24.521
and I kept it.

35:26.200 --> 35:28.726
I hid it under my bed.
I don't know why.

35:31.600 --> 35:32.681
And, uh...

35:32.880 --> 35:35.850
And Shelby, when they searched
the house, he found it,

35:35.920 --> 35:37.524
and he's got it, and
he won't give it back,

35:37.600 --> 35:39.409
and now he's got
Mom doing stuff,

35:40.240 --> 35:41.480
'cause she's afraid,
I guess.

35:41.880 --> 35:43.882
That's why you
broke into his house?

35:44.440 --> 35:45.965
Was to get that?
Yeah.

35:47.240 --> 35:48.241
Yeah, well,
what I found there...

35:48.320 --> 35:50.482
Well, at least what I
thought I found there

35:50.560 --> 35:53.040
was this girl.
This Asian girl.

35:53.920 --> 35:55.570
He was keeping her
locked in the basement.

35:58.800 --> 35:59.926
I couldn't get her
out of there.

36:00.000 --> 36:02.207
I told her I'd come
back and get her out.

36:04.200 --> 36:05.531
I'm gonna help you.

36:06.080 --> 36:07.081
Thank you.

36:08.200 --> 36:09.281
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

36:14.800 --> 36:16.040
Is that a girl?

36:17.440 --> 36:18.521
Is she pretty?

36:19.640 --> 36:20.801
You like her?

36:22.320 --> 36:24.049
Text her right now and tell
her you're coming over.

36:24.320 --> 36:26.322
I... I can't do that.
It just says, "Hey."

36:26.640 --> 36:28.768
Sure you can. What if she
doesn't want me to come over?

36:29.080 --> 36:31.287
Girls don't text you
at 10:00 at night

36:31.360 --> 36:32.964
because they don't want
you to come over.

36:33.320 --> 36:34.731
Go ahead. Trust me.

36:34.960 --> 36:37.008
I got laid when I was 12.
(CHUCKLES)

36:38.520 --> 36:41.126
Seriously, just text her.

36:48.680 --> 36:50.887
Oh, my... I can't
believe I just...

36:50.960 --> 36:52.724
I should never have
done that.

36:56.960 --> 36:58.041
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)

37:00.720 --> 37:01.801
(CLEARS THROAT)

37:05.440 --> 37:07.761
She says, "Cool.
Everyone's asleep.

37:07.840 --> 37:09.569
"I'm at my house.
Come over."

37:09.640 --> 37:10.721
Well, I can't go now.

37:10.800 --> 37:13.326
Not with all the...
It's crazy.

37:13.400 --> 37:15.323
Look, this is the only
thing that is not crazy.

37:16.120 --> 37:17.167
Okay?

37:17.480 --> 37:19.448
Be a 17-year-old
for five minutes.

37:20.200 --> 37:21.964
Come on, go have fun.
Right now?

37:22.040 --> 37:23.246
Yeah, right now.

37:23.720 --> 37:26.371
She's waiting for you, dumb-ass.
Come on, leave!

37:30.760 --> 37:32.171
(CHUCKLES) Go.

38:14.560 --> 38:15.721
Do you want to go
to my room?

38:16.200 --> 38:17.326
Where's your mom?

38:17.880 --> 38:19.120
Sedated.

38:32.520 --> 38:33.885
(CHUCKLES)

38:34.600 --> 38:36.090
You can sit on the bed.

38:55.200 --> 38:57.248
Thank you for
helping me so much.

38:58.720 --> 38:59.767
Sure.

39:10.520 --> 39:11.646
I'm just...

39:13.120 --> 39:14.770
Tired of being sad.

39:16.880 --> 39:19.770
I want to feel something
else for a little while.

39:21.600 --> 39:22.761
Do you think I'm weird?

39:24.680 --> 39:26.967
No, I don't think
you're weird.

39:28.840 --> 39:30.001
Thank you, Norman.

39:34.000 --> 39:35.161
It's my pleasure.

40:36.600 --> 40:37.806
(SIGHS)

40:55.200 --> 40:56.486
Norman, honey?

41:06.040 --> 41:07.280
Where's your brother?

41:08.520 --> 41:10.045
He's out with a girl.

41:11.120 --> 41:13.646
What the hell are you talking
about, "Out with a girl"?

41:13.720 --> 41:15.848
What girl?
He's with a girl, Norma.

41:16.760 --> 41:18.444
He's a 17-year-old kid,

41:18.520 --> 41:20.090
and he's out
with a girl he likes.

41:20.160 --> 41:22.003
And I hope to God
he's getting laid,

41:22.080 --> 41:23.366
because he sure as
hell deserves it

41:23.440 --> 41:24.805
for putting up
with your crazy ass.

41:24.880 --> 41:26.723
Putting up with my ass?

41:26.880 --> 41:28.291
Yeah. How dare you
say that about me!

41:28.360 --> 41:29.441
How dare you!

41:29.680 --> 41:31.921
What do you know about anything
between me and Norman?

41:32.000 --> 41:33.411
I know all
I need to know.

41:34.120 --> 41:36.566
I talked to Norman. Norman would
never say anything bad about me.

41:36.680 --> 41:38.011
He said plenty.
What would he say?

41:38.080 --> 41:39.491
Enough for him to be
taken away from you.

41:40.240 --> 41:42.368
Nobody is taking him
away from me.

41:42.440 --> 41:43.851
Oh, that girl is
right now!

41:45.560 --> 41:48.689
Oh, you stop it!
I hate you!

41:48.760 --> 41:50.091
I hate you!

41:50.160 --> 41:52.083
(GASPING AND CRYING)

41:55.760 --> 41:56.761
(DOORBELL RINGS)

42:00.760 --> 42:02.762
Norman?
(DOORBELL RINGS)

42:04.360 --> 42:06.124
Norman, is that you?

42:12.080 --> 42:13.445
Norma Louise Bates,
you're under arrest

42:13.520 --> 42:15.409
for the murder of
Keith Summers.

